gov.va.vinci.leo.descriptors

Class TypeDescriptionBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.vinci.leo.descriptors.TypeDescriptionBuilder

  • public class TypeDescriptionBuilder
extends Object
    Improve the Type building system in UIMA with a builder. To build a type, call create() first, then the type metadata. A simple example: 

            TypeDescriptionBuilder.create("gov.va.vinci.test.Type", "My Test Type", "uima.tcas.Annotation")
                                                                .addFeature("myFeature", "Feature", "String")
                                                                .addFeature("myFeature 2", "Feature 2", "String")
                                                                .getTypeDescription();
    Author:
    vhaislcornir

      • addFeature

        public TypeDescriptionBuilder addFeature(String aFeatureName,
                                         String aDescription,
                                         String aRangeTypeName,
                                         String aElementTypeName,
                                         Boolean aMultipleReferencesAllowed)
        Parameters:
        aFeatureName - name of feature to add
        aDescription - verbose description of the feature
        aRangeTypeName - name of feature's range type
        aElementTypeName - type of element expected to be contained in the array or list
        aMultipleReferencesAllowed - whether an array or list that's assigned to this feature can also be referenced from another feature. This is a Boolean object so that the null value can be used to represent the case where the user has not specified a value.
        Returns:
        this type description builder
